        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 2:40PM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 240 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 10 miles southeast of Greencastle to near
Brazil. Movement was south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brazil, Cloverdale, Knightsville, Harmony, Carbon, Reelsville, Lena,
and Belle Union.

This includes Interstate 70 between mile markers 26 and 49.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
